          <title>Diagnostic Imaging Report</title>
          <text>
            <paragraph>
              <content styleCode="Bold">Exam Type:</content> X-Ray, Right Knee (3 views: AP, Lateral, Sunrise)
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph>
              <content styleCode="Bold">Date of Exam:</content> 11/20/2025
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph>
              <content styleCode="Bold">Ordering Physician:</content> Dr. Thomas Chen, MD, FAAOS
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph>
              <content styleCode="Bold">Clinical Indication:</content>
              Chronic right knee pain, worsening with weight-bearing activity.
              Rule out osteoarthritis (ICD-10: M17.11).
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph>
              <content styleCode="Bold">Technique:</content>
              Three standard views of the right knee obtained standing and non-standing.
              Adequate technical quality. No prior studies available for comparison.
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph>
              <content styleCode="Bold">Findings:</content>
            </paragraph>
            <list>
              <item>Moderate to severe joint space narrowing in the medial compartment of the right knee.</item>
              <item>Prominent osteophyte formation at the medial tibial plateau and medial femoral condyle.</item>
              <item>Mild subchondral sclerosis of the medial tibial plateau.</item>
              <item>No acute fracture or dislocation identified.</item>
              <item>Patellofemoral compartment: mild joint space narrowing, small superior patellar osteophyte.</item>
              <item>Lateral compartment: preserved joint space.</item>
              <item>Soft tissue: no calcifications noted.</item>
            </list>
            <paragraph>
              <content styleCode="Bold">Impression:</content>
              Moderate-to-severe primary osteoarthritis of the right knee, predominantly medial
              compartment involvement. Kellgren-Lawrence Grade III–IV. Findings correlate with
              reported symptoms. Clinical correlation and orthopedic management recommended.
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph>
              <content styleCode="Bold">Recommendation:</content>
              Orthopedic consultation for consideration of corticosteroid injection versus
              total knee arthroplasty evaluation based on clinical examination and functional
              limitations.
            </paragraph>
          </text>
